WEBVTT

00:00.324 --> 00:02.300
Previously on
<i>Falling Skies...</i>

00:02.325 --> 00:03.250
We have to beat them.

00:03.275 --> 00:04.125
We will.

00:04.150 --> 00:06.278
We'll see each other again.
I promise.

00:06.303 --> 00:07.976
We can ally
with the rebel Skitters

00:08.000 --> 00:09.420
and hit the Overlords
with everything we got.

00:09.445 --> 00:11.489
I will <i>not</i>
<i>jeopardize this city --</i>

00:11.514 --> 00:12.637
I was told to find you --

00:12.662 --> 00:14.156
that you were the only one
who would understand.

00:14.181 --> 00:14.852
Who sent you?

00:14.877 --> 00:16.853
The one with the red eye --
the leader of the rebellion.

00:16.878 --> 00:17.971
Some of them
must have known

00:17.996 --> 00:19.793
that Tom would try to reach out
to his rebel Skitters.

00:19.818 --> 00:21.320
So you're locking us up?

00:21.345 --> 00:23.200
Drop your weapons
and step back!

00:23.225 --> 00:25.190
The civilian
government's been suspended.

00:25.215 --> 00:27.263
Charleston is
now under martial law.

00:27.288 --> 00:29.274
Your damned alliance
is gonna kill us all.

00:30.452 --> 00:32.104
You wanna make that rendezvous
with your rebel Skitters,

00:32.204 --> 00:34.004
I suggest you suck it up --
and fast.

00:35.047 --> 00:36.114
Nice work, boys.

00:36.148 --> 00:37.648
Looks like you dropped us

00:37.683 --> 00:40.681
in the middle
of a good, old-fashioned coup.

00:40.716 --> 00:42.016
Shut up, Pope.

00:42.051 --> 00:43.082
Why now, General?

00:43.117 --> 00:44.784
What were you waiting for?

00:44.819 --> 00:47.184
The perfect scapegoat?
The 2nd Mass?

00:47.218 --> 00:49.486
I've been waiting
for Dr. Manchester

00:49.520 --> 00:50.754
to come to his senses.

00:50.789 --> 00:52.524
And patiently,
I might add.

00:52.558 --> 00:54.895
And I was acting in the best
interest of our citizens.

00:54.929 --> 00:59.668
The people voted for civil rule,
not for a military junta.

00:59.702 --> 01:01.739
Don't be so naive,
Arthur.

01:01.773 --> 01:05.643
Eventually,
the aliens will find us.

01:05.678 --> 01:09.746
We have no choice <i>but</i> to go
on the offensive -- now.

01:11.884 --> 01:15.221
You with us...or not?

01:15.255 --> 01:16.889
Not this way.

01:16.924 --> 01:18.058
I'm sorry, General,

01:18.092 --> 01:19.760
but my vision
of the new United States

01:19.794 --> 01:21.762
doesn't begin
with a military coup.

01:21.797 --> 01:24.200
I'll agree that Arthur may have lost
sight of some of the original goals,

01:24.235 --> 01:27.604
but to put him in jail,
declare martial law?

01:27.639 --> 01:29.573
Your actions are misguided,
sir.

01:29.608 --> 01:32.211
I would have assumed,
given its reputation,

01:32.245 --> 01:34.980
the 2nd Mass
would be chomping at the bit

01:35.015 --> 01:37.684
for the chance
to take it to the enemy.

01:37.719 --> 01:40.888
I guess I assumed wrong.

01:40.923 --> 01:43.592
Lock them up!
Get them inside!

01:46.330 --> 01:48.699
Appreciate the solidarity,
Tom.

01:48.733 --> 01:50.902
This has nothing to do with you,
Arthur. Believe me.

01:52.972 --> 01:55.106
That's an outer security
perimeter breach!

01:55.141 --> 01:57.276
Let's move!
Let's move!

02:04.085 --> 02:05.953
Move! Move!

02:07.288 --> 02:08.622
Prepare to fire!

02:10.158 --> 02:11.226
Stand by!

02:14.129 --> 02:16.031
General, wait!
Those are the rebels.

02:16.065 --> 02:17.299
How can you be sure?

02:17.334 --> 02:18.968
The one with the red eye --
I know him.

02:19.002 --> 02:21.972
I said,
"prepare to fire"!

02:22.006 --> 02:24.174
Stop!

02:24.209 --> 02:26.377
We're not here
to hurt anyone.

02:26.411 --> 02:28.313
Ben.

02:32.852 --> 02:33.953
Are you all right?

02:33.987 --> 02:36.155
Ben!

02:36.189 --> 02:38.824
General, tell your men
to lower their weapons.

02:40.000 --> 02:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:08.826 --> 03:09.959
Sir?

03:22.040 --> 03:23.707
Hold your fire.

03:23.742 --> 03:24.875
Stand down!

03:27.806 --> 03:31.806
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Falling Skies 2x10 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>A More Perfect Union</font>
